# ── SendGrid Webhooks ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ECDSA public key from SendGrid Event Webhook settings for signature verification.
SENDGRID_WEBHOOK_KEY=""

# ── Email Deliverability (DNS records — configure in your DNS provider) ────
# These are NOT env vars. Configure them as DNS TXT records for your sending domain.
#
# SPF — Authorize SendGrid to send on your behalf:
#   TXT record on trysovereignai.com:
#   v=spf1 include:sendgrid.net ~all
#
# DKIM — SendGrid provides CNAME records during domain authentication:
#   Follow: SendGrid > Settings > Sender Authentication > Domain Authentication
#   Add the 3 CNAME records SendGrid generates to your DNS.
#
# DMARC — Policy for handling SPF/DKIM failures:
#   TXT record on _dmarc.trysovereignai.com:
#   v=DMARC1; p=quarantine; rua=mailto:dmarc-reports@trysovereignai.com; pct=100
#
# Domain Warmup:
#   New sending domains should follow the warmup schedule in src/lib/outreach/warmup.ts.
#   Start with low daily limits (5-10/day) and ramp up over 28 days.
#   The OutreachDomain model tracks warmup state automatically.

# ── Stripe Additional Webhooks ──────────────────────────────────────────────
